                	<h4 class=" editContent">Ramakrishna Mission, Dibrugarh</h4>
                    <p class="para editContent">A group of people inspired with the ideal of service preached by great Swami Vivekananda established Sri Ramakrishna Seva Samity, Dibrugarh in the year 1928 with the motive to educate marginalised kids by opening Night School. The Night School was started in a rented hut then situated at the very place where the present “RANGGHAR CINEMA HALL” stands. Later on in the year 1935 it was sifted to Shantipara Puja Mandap and activities like Charitable Dispensary, Lower Primary School along with Night School were run..</p>
